Class ProtocolParsing.StringParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.nashua.tt151.libraries.parsers.ProtocolParsing.StringParser
  • Enclosing class:
    ProtocolParsing

    public static final class ProtocolParsing.StringParser
extends Object
    This class is responsible for parsing messages sent from the laptop to the robot and vice versa. For more information on the protocol visit the wiki.

      • isQuery

        public static boolean isQuery(String msg)
        Tests if the message is a Query (aka Request). A Query message begins with the character Q and is not case-sensitive.
        Parameters:
        msg - The message to test
        Returns:
        True if the message is a query, false otherwise

      • getCommand

        public static ProtocolParsing.Command getCommand(String msg)
        An alternative to the above methods, this method gets the command from the message header rather than testing it.
        Parameters:
        msg - The message to get the command from
        Returns:
        An enumerator from Commands, unknown is returned if no other commands match

      • getKey

        public static ProtocolParsing.Key getKey(String msg)
        Identifies the key in the message. All of the possible keys are located on the wiki and are represented by the enum Keys. If no possible key was identified, Unknown is returned
        Parameters:
        msg - The message containing the key to retrieve
        Returns:
        An enumerator from Keys representing the key in the message

      • getValue

        public static String getValue(String msg)
        Gets the value from the message. The value varies based on the key. If a value was not identified, null is returned
        Parameters:
        msg - The message to get the value from
        Returns:
        A string containing the value.

      • getArgs

        public static String[] getArgs(String msg)
        Gets the additional args (if any) from the message. Arguments are separated by commas, after the final colon
        Parameters:
        msg - The message containing args (if any)
        Returns:
        An array of strings, representing the arguments

      • createMessage

        public static String createMessage(ProtocolParsing.Command command,
                   ProtocolParsing.Key key,
                   String value,
                   String[] args)
        Create a string to be transmitted over TCP. Query does not require a value or arguments (Leave value null). Arguments are NOT required.
        Parameters:
        command - A enumerator from Commands representing the command (Must not be Commands.Unknown)
        key - An enumerator from Keys representing the key (Must not be Keys.Unknown!)
        value - A string representing the value (Leave empty string if Query)
        args - A string of args to be added
        Returns:
        A String containing the message to be sent
